General Specs: Parker, Year 1921, 12 Gauge, 6lbs 15oz, Side by Side 

Serial Number: 196302 

Parker VH Grade 12 gauge guns are not rare, as they made over 50,000 of them. However, finding nice, untouched original VH Grades with 75% factory case color, 98% factory blue and wood finish, excellent screws and checkering, and perfect wood to metal fit is becoming exceedingly difficult. VH Grade guns were field guns and saw lots of use. There are few guns remaining that have not been worn thin, or restored in one way or another. This gun, sn196302 shipped in 1921 IS EXCEPTIONAL IN SEVERAL WAYS. First, it has the high factory original condition as noted above, and second, IT IS MADE ON A #1 FRAME, USUALLY RESERVED FOR 16 GAUGE GUNS. Most all 12ga. Parkers are made on a #1 1/2 or #2 frame and weigh considerably more than this 6lb. 13oz. gun that balances just 3/16" ahead of the hinge pin. Dynamic in hand with 14 3/8" LOP to the factory dogshead butt plate and high comb at 2 1/2" x 1 7/16" and neutral cast, sporting 28" M/F barrels with mirror bores, this gun is the upland gunners perfect late season shotgun. Great gun for sporting clays and with RST Shotshells "spreader" loads, will work for all seasons and games. One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.
